---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import DocsSidebar from "../../components/DocsSidebar.astro";
---
<Layout title="MCP server · flipagent docs">
	<div class="cmw cmw-bordered">
		<div class="docs-shell">
			<DocsSidebar />
			<article class="docs-content">
				<h1>MCP server</h1>
				<p class="lead">flipagent-mcp exposes the reseller API as MCP tools. Drop it into Claude Code and the agent can drive the whole cycle — sourcing, evaluate, buy, list, sell, fulfill — through conversation.</p>

				<h2>Install</h2>
				<p>The server runs through <code>npx</code>; nothing to install globally. The CLI writes the config in one go:</p>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`npx -y flipagent-cli init --mcp`}</code></pre></div>

				<h2>Manual config</h2>
				<p>Add the server to your MCP host's config file:</p>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`{
  "mcpServers": {
    "flipagent": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "flipagent-mcp"],
      "env": { "FLIPAGENT_API_KEY": "fa_free_xxx" }
    }
  }
}`}</code></pre></div>
				<p>Restart the host. The tools below show up in any chat.</p>

				<h2>Tools</h2>
				<p>Tool names follow <code>flipagent_&lt;verb&gt;_&lt;resource&gt;</code> (snake_case, action-leading). The <code>flipagent_</code> prefix keeps names collision-free when other MCP servers are loaded alongside. Marketplace stays a parameter — the same names work as Amazon and Mercari adapters land.</p>

				<h3>Toolsets</h3>
				<p>Tools group by domain so the host loads only what's needed. Default = <code>core</code>; opt in to others via <code>FLIPAGENT_MCP_TOOLSETS</code> (comma-separated, or <code>*</code> for everything).</p>
				<table class="api">
					<thead><tr><th>Toolset</th><th>Default</th><th>What it covers</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr><td><code>core</code></td><td>✅</td><td>Sourcing + decisions + buy + listing essentials + sale fulfillment + finance.</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>comms</code></td><td>⬜</td><td>Buyer comms — messages, offers, disputes, feedback.</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>forwarder</code></td><td>⬜</td><td>Package-forwarder ops via the flipagent extension (Planet Express today).</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>notifications</code></td><td>⬜</td><td>Webhooks + eBay platform notifications.</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>seller_account</code></td><td>⬜</td><td>Seller diagnostics — privilege, KYC, subscription, payments program, sales tax.</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>admin</code></td><td>⬜</td><td>Ship providers, location detail/delete + state toggles, browser-DOM escape hatch (<code>flipagent_query_browser</code>).</td></tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>

				<h3>Default tools (<code>core</code>)</h3>
				<table class="api">
					<thead><tr><th>Tool</th><th>Backed by</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Discovery</strong></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_get_capabilities</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/capabilities</code> — first call: what works for this api key right now</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_get_my_key</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/keys/me</code> — tier, quota</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_get_quota</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/me/quota</code> — eBay-side rate-limit budget</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_get_ebay_connection</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/connect/ebay/status</code></td></tr>

						<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Sourcing</strong></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_search_items</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/items/search</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_get_item</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/items/&#123;id&#125;</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_search_sold_items</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/items/search?status=sold</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_list_categories</code> / <code>flipagent_suggest_category</code> / <code>flipagent_list_category_aspects</code></td><td><code>/v1/categories/*</code></td></tr>

						<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Decisions + operations</strong></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_evaluate_item</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/evaluate</code> — one call returns a buy/hold/skip verdict on a listing</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_get_evaluate_job</code> / <code>flipagent_get_evaluation_pool</code></td><td><code>/v1/evaluate/*</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_quote_shipping</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/ship/quote</code></td></tr>

						<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Buy</strong></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_create_purchase</code> / <code>flipagent_get_purchase</code> / <code>flipagent_cancel_purchase</code></td><td><code>/v1/purchases/*</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_list_bids</code> / <code>flipagent_place_bid</code> / <code>flipagent_list_biddable_listings</code></td><td><code>/v1/bids/*</code></td></tr>

						<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Listing prerequisites + CRUD</strong></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_create_media_upload</code> / <code>flipagent_get_media</code></td><td><code>/v1/media/*</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_list_policies</code> / <code>flipagent_list_policies_by_type</code></td><td><code>/v1/policies/*</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_list_locations</code> / <code>flipagent_upsert_location</code></td><td><code>/v1/locations/*</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_create_listing</code> / <code>flipagent_update_listing</code> / <code>flipagent_relist_listing</code> / <code>flipagent_preview_listing_fees</code></td><td><code>/v1/listings/*</code></td></tr>

						<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Sale fulfillment + finance</strong></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_list_sales</code> / <code>flipagent_ship_sale</code></td><td><code>/v1/sales/*</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_list_payouts</code> / <code>flipagent_list_transactions</code></td><td><code>/v1/payouts</code>, <code>/v1/transactions</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_list_recommendations</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/recommendations</code></td></tr>

						<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Programs</strong></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_list_programs</code> / <code>flipagent_opt_in_program</code> / <code>flipagent_opt_out_program</code></td><td><code>/v1/me/programs/*</code> — required before policy creation works</td></tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>

				<h2>Error remediation</h2>
				<p>Every API error response that the caller can fix (OAuth not done, extension not paired, server-side env not configured) carries <code>next_action: &#123; kind, url, instructions &#125;</code>. The MCP renders this directly into <code>isError: true</code> content — relay the text to the end user and they'll know exactly where to go.</p>

				<h2>Compose your own logic</h2>
				<p>Tools are typed and orthogonal. <code>flipagent_evaluate_item</code> is the all-in-one tool: pass an itemId and one call returns a buy/hold/skip verdict with profit and demand signals. Agents can also chain low-level tools (<code>flipagent_search_items</code> → <code>flipagent_search_sold_items</code> → <code>flipagent_evaluate_item</code> → <code>flipagent_quote_shipping</code>) to assemble custom reselling workflows. See the <a href="/docs/coverage/">eBay coverage</a> page for what's wrapped and the <a href="/docs/api/">API reference</a> for request shapes.</p>
			</article>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
